<br>
My issue with these quests is that players had no way of &quot;planning&quot; ahead to accomodate these quests. How could they? SoL wasn't out yet. So the players 35 and over are prevented from completing it.<br>
<br>
Roleplaying it through. Well, I know people think they can just hire folks to go get items for them that they need for quests, but have you tried to do this? The language barrier combined with the low popualtion of this server makes it nearly impossible. I hear what you are saying and actaully agree with you about this being what verant intended, but you should also keep in mind that verant expected a larger server population to accomodate this. At the very least they expected the &quot;merchant&quot; feature to be working to help overcome the language barrier. Unfortunately the population they expected didnt materialize and we are still waiting for the merchant feature.<br>
<br>
I am repeating myself by saying this but I will again. The bottomline is that the TLC is affecting many players in ways that verant could not foresee. As new expansions and new quests are released these problems will continue to grow. I don't want TLC removed, but I do want it modified. Brad's last comment before he removed the TLC was they were going to work on an alternate form of TLC. Unfortunatley we don't know if thats still the case now that he is gone.<br>
<br>
I strongly encourage you to go out and try some of the new quests in SoL. It will not only get you to explore the new zones (which is alot of fun) but will undoubtedly expose you to the issues that we have mentioned.<br>
<br>
<br>
